latestPosts.caption:
This might just be my new favorite milk tea spot in Bellevue! First off, the prices are 👀, the tea quality is chef’s kiss 😋, and the branding? Absolutely adorable 💗 What more could you ask for?

📍 @mollytea_bellevue 
103 Bellevue Way NE, Bellevue, WA 98004

One of my favorite hidden gems in Bellevue! 🍣 

@mix_sushi_bar serves up some of the tastiest seared salmon I’ve ever had! It’s my go-to order along with their unagi bowl—but this time, I switched things up and tried a few new items, and I’m officially a fan.

Their “trash roll” (a California roll topped with their house-made chili oil) is insanely addictive, and I love that they offer a wide variety of vegetarian rolls that are just as flavorful. With so many options to choose from, you really can’t go wrong here.

It’s truly a hidden gem tucked inside a food court, but the secret’s out—definitely give them a try if you haven’t already. For food court sushi, this place is next level! 🍣🔥

📍Mix Sushi Bar
2 locations in Bellevue:
- 15600 NE 8th St, Ste PM41, Bellevue, WA 98008
- 500 Bellevue Way NE, Fl 2, Bellevue, WA 98004

If you’ve ever been to Don Quijote in Japan, you need to check out @tesolife 🤩 it’s basically @donki_jp_en meets Hmart, Uwajimaya, T&T, and Pop Mart all in one spot! Their grand opening is July 8th, and trust me, you’ll want to be there early.

They’re the only place I’ve found selling Labubu at the OG price of $21.99! The plushies, the figurines, the POPMART selection… I was in collector heaven. And don’t even get me started on the skincare and makeup section, Japanese, Korean, Chinese brands galore. I was seriously overstimulated (in the best way possible) and stayed way too long.

Oh, and yes, they even have claw machines. Just go see it for yourself! You won’t regret it! 👏💖🧸🛍️✨

Grand Opening July 8th, 11am-9pm
📍32015 S Pacific Hwy, Federal Way, WA 98003

Opening event: 
🎁 free gifts with every purchase 
🎁 premium freebies when you spend $50, $100, $150, or $200

#tesolife#popmart#sponsored

My fave ramen spot just dropped a summer menu and it might be the best ramen I’ve had in WA! 😮‍💨 I’m at @menyamusashius in their Kirkland location —famous for tsukemen, but this time I went for their chilled Summer Tantanmen: a creamy, soupless mazemen packed with spicy pork, cilantro, and a big ol’ lemon wedge for that zesty kick. 🔥

Also tried their new steamed baos (karaage, croquette, ebi, chashu)—all kid friendly and bomb. The orange chicken? Super crispy and juicy. And the matcha soft serve with red bean taiyaki? So good I’m still thinking about it. 🍵

Finished it off with a spin at the vending machine and won a keychain 🙌 the Summer Menu is only exclusive to their Kirkland location*

📍Menya Musashi
Locations in Kirkland, CapHill, Federal Way

@trophycupcakes is dropping an exclusive Labubu Blind Box Cupcake this Saturday, June 28 at their University Village location!

Each cupcake is sealed in a mystery box — some feature frosted classics, others come with surprise loot like Trophy gift cards, and one ultra-rare box holds a golden ticket with a sweet prize.

Only 24 dozen available — limit 4 per guest. Get ready for exclusive giveaways, a special Lychee Berry Chaos Slushie, and more surprises!

📍 Trophy Cupcakes – University Village
📅 Saturday, June 28
🕙 Doors open at 10AM | Line starts at 8AM

Don’t miss this one-of-a-kind drop!

Of all the Costco’s I’ve been to around the world, my favorite has to be Shanghai, China’s Costco! 

#costco #costcofinds #costcochina #costcodeals #costcobuys

Completely obsessed with @toptoy_america plushies right now 🧸💖 They’re ridiculously soft, super cute, and the variety?? Endless. My current fave is the Gyun-Gyun Lamb series — you can snag them on Amazon: https://bit.ly/3FF19et 🐑✨

If you’re into Sanrio or other adorable collections, check out their site: www.gotoptoy.com 💻

Not gonna lie… I think I’ve started a new addiction and I’m not even mad about it 😭🫶

Let me know if you want it shorter or more sales-focused!
Don’t ask me how long I was at this Costco 😂 #costcochina #shanghaicostco #costcofinds
